cp|red|at|^*bOliverC:^*n|cp||at|  Hi Everyone and welcome to today's Precision Club session, in which we'll be taking a close look at
the 2@D Opening & Responses that we use in this system.


This is  ^*bNOT^*n a standard Precision Opening.


If you have not already done so, please have a look at the notes I have prepared on Precision Club bidding.

You can find these on: ^*hhttp://ocp.pigpen.org.uk/index.php^*n

You might want to have these onscreen in the background for reference during the session.

The notes on 2@D can be found at  ^*hhttp://ocp.pigpen.org.uk/2d.php^*n  



Ok, first a brief introduction to the 2@D Opening...

"Classic" Precision uses the 2@D Opening for  11-15  4414  shape hands  ie. with only a singleton Diamond.

Devoting a bid to a single shape that only comes up one hand in a thousand is a waste of a bid, in my view, which is why I have always preferred to open such hands with 1@D  instead, which in turn frees up the 2@D Opening for something else.    
